Reasoning: The paper discusses techniques and algorithms for optimizing data transfers across geographically dispersed datacenters over inter-datacenter networks. This involves network infrastructure, communication protocols, and optimization algorithms, which are all relevant to the computer networks (cs.NI) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) sub-categories. The paper also discusses admission control and multicast transfers, which are relevant to the systems and control (cs.SY) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. Finally, the paper presents a generalized optimization framework, which is relevant to the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category.
